摘 要 
在循环经济与“双碳”战略背景下，传统旧衣回收模式存在效率低下、流程不透明和公众参与难等问题。本课题设计并实现了一个基于前后端分离架构的“互联网+旧衣回收”系统。后端使用Python Flask微框架，结合Flask-RESTful扩展提供标准化RESTful API，并运用Flask-SQLAlchemy进行数据建模，确保业务逻辑清晰与数据安全高效。前端采用双端分离策略：用户端为微信小程序，提供便捷的预约和追踪服务；管理后台使用Vue.js 3与Element-Plus组件库开发，构建动态管理界面。系统核心数据存储在MySQL中，并引入Redis缓存高频访问数据，显著提升响应速度。论文遵循软件工程规范，详细阐述需求分析、架构设计、数据库建模、模块化编码和系统测试的全过程。黑盒与接口测试表明，系统功能完整、运行稳定、界面友好，验证了“互联网+环保”模式的技术可行性，为废旧纺织品的规范化回收提供了实用的数字化解决方案。
关键词： 旧衣回收系统；Python Flask；Vue.js；微信小程序；前后端分离；RESTful API；可持续消费


ABSTRACT
In the context of the circular economy and the “dual carbon” strategy, traditional used-clothing recycling models suffer from low efficiency, lack of process transparency, and limited public participation. This project designs and implements an “Internet + Used Clothing Recycling” system based on a front-end/back-end separation architecture.The back-end is built using the Python Flask microframework, combined with the Flask-RESTful extension to provide standardized RESTful APIs, and utilizes Flask-SQLAlchemy for data modeling to ensure clear business logic as well as secure and efficient data management. The front-end adopts a dual-interface strategy: the user side is developed as a WeChat Mini Program, offering convenient reservation and tracking services; the administrative dashboard is built with Vue.js 3 and the Element Plus component library to create a dynamic management interface. The system stores core data in MySQL and incorporates Redis to cache high-frequency data, significantly improving response speed. Following software engineering best practices, this study systematically elaborates on the entire development process, including requirements analysis, architectural design, database modeling, modular coding, and system testing. Black-box and API testing results demonstrate that the system is functionally complete, stable in operation, and user-friendly, validating the technical feasibility of the “Internet + Environmental Protection” model and providing a practical digital solution for the standardized recycling of waste textiles.
